	Righteous! - version 0.7.1
	(atomskninja@gmail.com)

Created by Ben Hull and released under the GNU GPL

Game Description
================
Move the falling blocks to form groups of four squares of the 
same type. Once you have done this the highlited squares will be
removed by the moving metronome. If a block gets stuck above the 
game grid then the game is over. 
Try to build up combos for massive points!
	

System Requirements
===================
X Windows for linux
SDL, SDL_image, and SDL_mixer (www.libsdl.org)
tested on linux but probably will compile on others


Controls
========
Left/Right arrow - move, adjust time limit in menu
Up/Down arrow - rotate blocks, change selection in menu
Spacebar - fall faster
f - enable/disable fullscreen
m - enable/disable background music
h - enable/disable HUDless mode
s - impose a sane framerate :)
ESC - quit to the menu
Return - pause/unpause the game, make selection in menu
Control/Alt keys - enable rapid movement


